ifferent about the initialization behavior.\n\nThe source also includes visual diagrams showing examples of the test data and response count changes, but those can be skipped since they're just illustrations of the concepts already described.\n\nFor section 3, I'm examining the XML configuration structure that defines file path settings, particularly how it maps the test data file location to a property key. I'm noticing the XML structure closes properly in the knowledge file, though the source itself seems to have a missing closing tag for the component element. Let me verify the knowledge file statements against the original source to check for any fabrications—specifically looking at how the mock class description is worded compared to what's actually stated in the source material. I'm comparing the log output formats between the source map and knowledge file to verify they match, checking both the message framework headers and body content across different message types like the messaging send operations. I'm seeing the document structure now—there are several subsections under the main Excel file writing section, covering everything from formatting examples and message structure to file placement and logging, plus additional sections on framework class configuration and library setup for the unit tests. I'm working through the RST hierarchy structure for this document. The title uses `===`, then there are two main sections both marked with `---` underlines: the first about mock classes for unit testing, and the second about framework class configuration. But I'm noticing the second section actually uses `~~~` underlines, which would make it a subsection level rather than a main section level. I'm working through the RST heading hierarchy more carefully now. Since the dashes appear first in the document, they establish the h2 level, which makes all the tilde-delimited sections h3 subsections. That means `フレームワークで使用するクラスの設定` is also at the h3 level, not a separat